		<div class="qna-section" style="padding-bottom:20px;">
			<div class="question">Question 7:Any extra advice to your juniors for technical skills that they should develop?</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer: For folks of first year I will strongly suggest to explore as much as you can. Look in to all sorts of technical domains and take your time of an year or so and find out the domain which excites you the most. As you all are not in the college right now you are missing a lot in the fun part but you should not lag behind in the technical aspect as you will surey have all the "college fun" from the very first day you come to BIT but you won't ever get the huge amount of time you have now. When the college opens you will have a heavy workload and may be even weekends will be working days. You should talk with your seniors from k18 & k19 to get an understanding of what kind of projects to work on. Being in your homes you could very comfortably start with AI related stuffs but I will strongle suggest to talk with k18 & k19 and get some guidance. It would be great if you can work on Robot Operating System (ROS), AI based image processing, designing mechanical systems on SolidWorks, development of cool stuffs on Blender etc. You should get yourself comfortable with GIT. Join one of the many prestigious clubs of our college & rest will be history :)</div>
